physical_examinations.relevant_findings: GEN: Alert & oriented, no acute distress. HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucus membranes moist. CV: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs or gallops or rubs. PULM: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes, rales, or rhonchi. ABD: Soft, tender in right lower quadrant and left lower quadrant, no guarding or rebound, no peritoneal signs.
